title: For Sale:  Pre-Rifle Dynamics Jim Fuller AKM w/ Magpul Furniture
postcontent: For sale is a pre-Rifle Dynamics Jim Fuller AKM in 7.62x39mm, built solely by Mr. Fuller himself in 2008. It's built on a Nodak Spud NDS-1 receiver using a Romanian G parts kit hand-picked by Gabe Suarez of One Source Tactical. The rifle has all of Jim Fuller's custom features, including:• Tuned Custom G2 Trigger• Tuned Action - Rails, Bolt, Carrier & Trigger assembly• Modified Fuller Rear Sight• Dehorn Entire Rifle• Black Norrell's Moly Resin over Parkerization• Magpul MOE AK Stock• Magpul MOE AKM Handguard• Magpul QD Sling sockets (handguard and stock) • Side Scope Mount• US Palm AK Battle Grip• Wolverine Flash Hider• Krebs Custom SafetyThis rifle also has about 100 rounds through it, basically for sighting in and a day at the range. The rifle is immaculate inside and out with no finish wear. If you know who Jim Fuller is, then you know what kind of rifle this is. Given that this rifle is built early in Mr. Fuller’s career and Romanian G parts kits are rare, this rifle is a collectible item. Plus, there’s no wait for a true Rifle Dynamics AK. The price is $1595 plus $50 shipping. The preferred method of payment is a bank cashier’s check.Additional info:I have the ORIGINAL Romanian G leftover parts including stock, forend, safety, piston, trigger, grips, etc too. I'll throw that in for free. I am the original person who ordered and purchased the rifle from Jim. I had Gabe at OST hand-pick the Romanian G parts kit and ship it directly to Jim. The rest of the parts came from OST and Jim himself. There is no "Rifle Dynamics" wording etched into the receiver. He was not doing that at that time, because the Rifle Dynamics company did not exist yet. This rifle was built before the company existed. The parts kit this rifle was built from did not come with a side scope rail originally. I had Jim install one when he built it just in case I wanted to use it. I have the original receipt from Jim that details the build. I also have the receipt from Gabe at OST detailing all of the parts I purchased from him and had shipped directly to Jim (parts kit, stock set, internal parts, etc). I also have the original rifle build bag that Jim used to keep track of this build order.

postcontent:
Ruger New Model Single Six 22LR
 
This is a Ruger New Model Single-Six Single-action Revolver chambered for the ever popular.22 Long Rifle [LR] cartridge. The Single-Six is currently produced as the New Model Single-Six. The term "New Model" simply means that this model includes Ruger's transfer bar mechanism for increased safety, allowing one to carry the revolver safely with all 6 chambers loaded. Prior to 1973, the Single-Six was produced without the transfer bar mechanism, making it less safe to carry with all six chambers loaded, and with the hammer resting on a loaded chamber. The transfer bar safety allows the weapon to fire only when the trigger has been pulled. Ruger provides the transfer bar safety upgrade free of charge for owners of any old model Single-Six.
This example of the Single-Six features the 5.5" barrel, blued finish, and walnut wood stocks. The serial number places it in 1982 production year,69-204XX.  This does NOT have the 22 Mag cylinder.  There is no box the manual is available at Ruger.com.
The weapon is in excellent shape for being 34 years old.  The cylinder does have a faint line on it.  The  RUGER® NEW MODEL SINGLESIX® revolvers chambered for .22 long rifle are intended to be used with any standard make of .22 long rifle, long or short ammunition in either regular, high velocity or hyper-velocity loading.

title: For Sale:  Custom, Attorney Drafted NFA Gun Trust
postcontent: I am an Arkansas licensed attorney and offer comprehensive, custom NFA gun trust drafting services. My trusts are 20+ pages and cover the numerous issues related to NFA items for you and your beneficiaries. A gun trust enables you to purchase suppressors, short barreled rifles and fully automatic rifles without the hassles (and often impossibility) of a chief law enforcement officer signature as well as other bureaucratic red tape. As a firearms enthusiast, I want to see more people enjoying the benefits of NFA items and, because this isn't my primary source of income, I can offer my services at $199 for a trust. This includes an initial in-person or phone consultation to determine how to best serve your needs, all fees and documents, an electronic copy of your final trust documents, a guide to how to best use your trust as well as an appendix of ATF advisory letters and forms. While there are cheaper “fill-in-the-blank” trusts available online, the ATF has given negative feedback on many of these as not being well drafted and having the potential to expose the user to criminal and civil penalties. Not only am I licensed and in good standing in Arkansas, but I am also licensed and in good standing in Florida and Texas and can assist with trusts in those states as well.
